http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Vijayawada/Legal-counselling-to-be-offered-to-victims-of-violence/article13993696.ece

Joint Secretary in the Ministry of Women Development and Child Welfare (WD&CW) Sarada Khan on Sunday visited One-Stop-Centre, a rehabilitation centre set up by the Centre to help rape and domestic violence victims.The official, along with Joint Director (JD) of WD&CW Nazneen Bansaid a Central administrator, IT staff, police facilitator and a case worker had been appointed to help the victims. Medical treatment and legal and psychological counselling will be offered to victims of sexual assault, dowry harassment and domestic violence victims, officials said. Also, necessary training will be offered to victims in soft skills and maintenance of records, they added.